The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 EIH recast plan put on fast track

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, June 8: Shareholders of EIH Ltd today approved the transfer of two properties in Shimla and Bhubaneswar to EIH Associated Hotels Ltd, as part of the first round of restructuring within the group.

 According to the scheme of reconstruction, two properties of EIH, The Oberoi Shimla and the Trident Hilton in Bhubaneswar, have been transferred to EIH Associated.

 EIH Associated Hotels, promoted by the Oberois and Rahejas, will pay Rs 78 crore to its parent company. 

 Also, it will allot EIH Ltd 4 per cent redeemable non-cumulative preference shares of Rs 100 each and 6 per cent redeemable unsecured debentures of Rs 100 each.

 This will strengthen EIH Associated, improve its bottomline and also benefit EIH Ltd as it is one of the promoters, said S.S. Mukherjee, managing director, EIH Ltd.

 As part of the restructuring scheme, EIH Associated has been amalgamated with Indus Hotels Corporation Ltd.

 EIH Associated will issue Indus Hotelss shareholders one equity share of Rs 10 for every nine equity shares of Rs 10 each held by them in Indus. 




